This paper is primarily focused on computer vision, specifically fine-grained visual recognition. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and their training, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of gradient-based inversion techniques, which falls under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the model on various datasets, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
